    <p>Danc­ing At Dusk – A Mo­ment With Pina Bausch’s The Rite Of Spring</p>
    <p>In this film, Ger­man chore­og­ra­pher Pina Bausch’s iconic dance work, The Rite Of Spring, is per­formed in an ex­tra­or­di­nary set­ting – on a beach in Toubab Dialaw, Sene­gal. Filmed as the world went into lock­down, this per­for­mance cap­tures the last re­hearsal of a spe­cially as­sem­bled com­pany of 38 dancers from 14 African coun­tries as they pre­pared for an in­ter­na­tional tour. The spe­cial screen­ing also fea­tures in­ter­views with the cre­ative team, dancers and the Pina Bausch Foun­da­tion, a char­ity.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Avail­able on­line till Oct 31 ADMISSION: $12</p>
    <p>INFO: www.es­planade.com</p>
    <p>Rasas 2020: Dances From Bali</p>
    <p>Ba­li­nese dance group Eka Suwara San­thi present clas­si­cal dances that date back to the 17th cen­tury and more con­tem­po­rary pieces from the last few decades. The group will also per­form Tari Topeng, an an­cient masked dance that is re­quired at Ba­li­nese temple fes­ti­vals.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Avail­able on­line till Oct 31</p>
    <p>ADMISSION: Free INFO: www.es­planade.com</p>


